      • getRootDocNode

        protected org.dom4j.Node getRootDocNode(java.lang.String queueId)
                                 throws java.lang.Exception
        Retrieves the root document node from the batch XML. If the batch file path is for a directory, meaning that there are multiple batch xml files with only one document a piece, then each xml will be parsed. If there is a single batch xml, meaning that there are multiple documents in the file, then the xml will be parsed one time and stored as an instance member dom. The dom is eligibilized for garbage collection in the doDisconnect() method.
        Throws:
        java.lang.Exception

      • getBatchFilePath

        protected java.lang.String getBatchFilePath(java.lang.String queueId)
        Retrieves the file path to the file that contains the document(s). If the injected batchFilePath represents a directory, it is assumed multi file support is enabled and uses the injected prefix and suffix and queue id to determine the file name.

        Retrieves all of the values for the selected attribute in the xpath query. The qualification in the xpath query is dynamically built for each attribute being evaluated.

      • getAttributeDataType

        protected java.lang.String getAttributeDataType(org.dom4j.Node rootDocNode,
                                                java.lang.String docId,
                                                java.lang.String attrName)
        Retrieves the data type of the attribute. If an xpath query is configured, a value will attempt to be retrieved using it. If a value is found, that value is returned. If the value is not found, the default value is returned.

      • getSingleValue

        protected java.lang.String getSingleValue(org.dom4j.Node rootNode,
                                          java.lang.String xQuery,

        Based on the determination of whether the query is for node or attribute, the root node of the document is queried and result is cast to necessary type to retrieve the value.

      • getContentFilePath

        protected java.lang.String getContentFilePath(java.lang.String fileName,
                                              java.lang.String docExtension,
                                              org.dom4j.Node rootNode,
                                              java.lang.String docId)
        Builds the file path to the content file of the document. If the injected xpath query to find the content file's path location is not set, default it to look at the run time options for the base path and append the object name as the document name. In cases where the content file path must be built, checks to ensure a trailing slash is appeneded to the end. Ensures that the file exists. Assumes that if the path is retrieved via an xpath query that the proper file extension is attached. Also assumes for the case of no xpath query that the docName has the file extension attached.

      • getFileExtension

        protected java.lang.String getFileExtension(java.lang.String docName,
                                            org.dom4j.Node rootDocNode,
                                            java.lang.String docId)
        Determines the default file extension. If an xpath query was injected to find the extension it will query the document' dom object. If no xpath query was injected, by default will attempt to recover doc extension by parsing the document name (i.e. document_name.pdf - returns .pdf)
